snippet.textDisplay: Doonger we call in Sindhi is peak point of any big mountain and the survivor of this folk story named “ sasuhi “ she is saying to the mountain she grumble or complaining to the mountain that do not give me the pain please I am in my last stage, she is going in the search of “punhoon” her lover In the story, this is very interesting and inspiring story written in poetry of the great poet hazrat shah Abdul latif bhittai “bhittai” means who was living at the some range  of sand we call it   Bhitt in pure and old Sindhi language hazrat shah Abdul Latif bhittai has written many folk stories in his poetry some of these are sung here in Coke studio like “moomal Rano, Umar marvi”   I belong to This soil 🇵🇰🙏🏻❤️
